@prefix : <http://glossary.orcfax.io/#> .
@prefix skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
:assetPair
    skos:prefLabel "asset pair"@en;
    skos:definition '''
      An asset pair serves as a synonym for two values expressed as a
      BASE-QUOTE pair in Orcfax documentation. A BASE-QUOTE pair
      comprises two assets and indicates the value of the BASE asset
      when converted to the QUOTE asset. For example, in a FACT-ADA
      pair, a value of 0.77 signifies that one FACT is equivalent
      to 0.77 ADA.
    ''' ;
    skos:related :baseQuote.
